# CC PROMPT — v2.34.9 — feat(agents): inject MCP tool signatures into prompt to stop kwarg hallucination

## Evidence

Recurring failure across multiple traces:

- **2026-04-17 14:54** (execute task) — `service_health() got an unexpected keyword argument 'service_name'`, `service_health() missing 1 required positional argument: 'name'`, `elastic_kafka_logs() got an unexpected keyword argument 'pattern'`, `elastic_error_logs() got an unexpected keyword argument 'since_minutes'`, `service_current_version() got an unexpected keyword argument 'service_name'`. Six signature errors in one 8-tool task.
- **2026-04-17 16:21** (Logstash sub-agent) — `kafka_consumer_lag() missing 1 required positional argument: 'group'`. Last substantive call burned on a signature error.

The agent has the tool names in the allowlist. It does not have the
parameter signatures. The LLM is pattern-matching from training data or from
adjacent tool names and guessing — `since_minutes` instead of `minutes_ago`,
`service_name` instead of `name`, `pattern` instead of `query`. Each miss
costs a full tool call.

Fix: materialise the real signatures (from the MCP manifest) into the
agent system prompt, so the agent sees the exact parameter names before it
calls.

